2. cs.SI - The study involves investigating the relationship between human resource management practices and retail productivity, which can be seen as a social system. This falls under the scope of social intelligence. 
3. cs.LG - The use of machine learning algorithms and techniques may be involved in the development of the intelligent agents and the simulation model. 
4. cs.CYBER - The study may involve cybersecurity concerns related to the use of intelligent agents in a retail context. 
5. cs.HC - The study may involve human-computer interaction considerations in the design and implementation of the simulation model.
